NAME
    Acme::CPANModules::EscapingAndQuoting - Various modules that
    escape/quote data to make it safe

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.002 of
    Acme::CPANModules::EscapingAndQuoting (from Perl distribution
    Acme-CPANModules-EscapingAndQuoting), released on 2019-12-24.

DESCRIPTION
    Various modules that escape/quote data to make it safe.

INCLUDED MODULES
    *   HTML::Entities

    *   URI::Escape

        Alternate modules: URI::Escape::XS

    *   String::PodQuote

    *   String::ShellQuote

        Alternate modules: Win32::ShellQuote, ShellQuote::Any,
        ShellQuote::Any::Tiny

    *   String::ShellQuote

    *   String::Escape

    *   String::JS

    *   Unicode::Escape

    *   TeX::Encode

    *   String::PerlQuote

    *   MIME::Base64

    *   Data::Clean

    *   Data::Clean::ForJSON

FAQ
  What are ways to use this module?
    Aside from reading it, you can install all the listed modules using
    cpanmodules:

        % cpanmodules ls-entries EscapingAndQuoting | cpanm -n

    or Acme::CM::Get:

        % perl -MAcme::CM::Get=EscapingAndQuoting -E'say $_->{module} for @{ $LIST->{entries} }' | cpanm -n

    This module also helps lcpan produce a more meaningful result for "lcpan
    related-mods" when it comes to finding related modules for the modules
    listed in this Acme::CPANModules module.

